        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 7:28PM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Little Eagle, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Little Eagle and Mahto.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
